{"session_id":"svc-1779873714932667504","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-27T09:21:55.841120189Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"haiku","sticky":{"key_present":true,"assignment":"not_applicable","bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"resolved_harness":"claude","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"haiku","work_dir":"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-f9ddaa68-20260527T092129-ee89e738","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead in an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the contract: every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Too big if any holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across ~5+ files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, use a split-first pass.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, children once more; reject third-level splits with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child (copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;`.\u0026#xA;4. Write `no_changes_rationale.txt` under the bead metadata `bundle` path with child IDs, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Decomposition alone is success. Do not mix it with implementation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC to concrete evidence (test, file, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Run git/index mutations sequentially; do not use parallel tool calls for `git add`, `git commit`, or other staging/commit commands.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- If `lefthook run pre-commit` depends on staged files, rerun it after staging the exact commit set. A `no-staged-files` run is not acceptance evidence.\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- Current-bead lifecycle is orchestrator-owned. Do not run `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --claim`, `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --status \u0026lt;status\u0026gt;`, `ddx bead update \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt; --unclaim`, or `ddx bead close \u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;`. Step 0 still allows `ddx bead create`, `ddx bead dep add`, and `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;`.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `no_changes_rationale.txt` under the bead metadata `bundle` path before exiting. No commit or rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The `no_changes_rationale.txt` file under the bead metadata `bundle` path must contain one of:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` are rejected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;For orchestrator decomposition, add `orchestrator_action: decompose` alongside `status: open`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Reports go under the bead metadata `bundle` path in `.ddx/executions/`. **Never write reports to `/tmp` or outside the repo**. Use a named in-repo path when given; otherwise write `\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md` there. Commit it with the code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other instruction files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-f9ddaa68\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003epre_claim_intake decoder rejects readiness_checks.verdict=bool; entire fizeau queue idle\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;ddx work --watch\u0026#39;s pre-claim intake decoder fails to unmarshal the readiness_checks response when verdict is a JSON bool. Every claim attempt produces the same warn-only rejection, so the worker logs a warning and skips. With 23 ready beads in the fizeau queue and one fizeau-scoped daemon, the entire queue is idle indefinitely.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;OBSERVATION (Fizeau, 2026-05-18 05:27-05:39 UTC; about an hour after the previous wedge bug ddx-8f2e0ebf)\u0026#xA;- Worker: PID 1527216, ddx work --watch in /Users/erik/Projects/fizeau, etime 01:22:40 at observation.\u0026#xA;- Log: /Users/erik/Projects/fizeau/.ddx/agent-logs/agent-loop-1779077845655338391.jsonl\u0026#xA;- Pattern every ~50s: resource.preflight (status ok) -\u0026gt; pre_claim_intake.start -\u0026gt; pre_claim_intake.warn -\u0026gt; loop.idle.\u0026#xA;- Sample pre_claim_intake.warn payload:\u0026#xA;  {\u0026#xA;    \u0026#34;bead_id\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;fizeau-5b2a8950\u0026#34;,\u0026#xA;    \u0026#34;decision\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;warn\u0026#34;,\u0026#xA;    \u0026#34;decision_source\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;pre_claim_intake\u0026#34;,\u0026#xA;    \u0026#34;detail\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;decode result: json: cannot unmarshal bool into Go struct field .readiness_checks.verdict of type string\u0026#34;,\u0026#xA;    \u0026#34;fingerprint\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;15155a1cd44e96daf53eabb14c8eb3ccd8b0e5271d881208cfcbbf2869899f4f\u0026#34;,\u0026#xA;    \u0026#34;outcome\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;intake_error\u0026#34;,\u0026#xA;    \u0026#34;policy_mode\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;warn-only\u0026#34;,\u0026#xA;    \u0026#34;reason\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;system_unready\u0026#34;,\u0026#xA;    \u0026#34;rule_id\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;pre_claim_intake.system_unready\u0026#34;,\u0026#xA;    \u0026#34;suggested_action\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;check the readiness route or harness configuration and retry\u0026#34;,\u0026#xA;    \u0026#34;system_reason\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;unavailable\u0026#34;\u0026#xA;  }\u0026#xA;- Identical fingerprint across multiple bead_ids confirms it is a schema mismatch, not a bead-specific issue.\u0026#xA;- Queue state at observation: open=44, ready=23, dependency-waiting=19. None of the 23 ready beads got claimed in the prior 30 minutes; commit log empty for the same window.\u0026#xA;- Other beads (fizeau-a15106ab, fizeau-90b85c8b) WERE successfully closed earlier in the night through some other path (perhaps a different worker version or a different execute-bead invocation). Suggests this decoder bug appeared mid-session OR only affects certain readiness routes.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;WHY THIS IS A BUG\u0026#xA;1. Schema drift between the readiness-check producer and the pre_claim_intake consumer. One emits verdict as bool, the other parses it as string. Either the producer or consumer changed without coordination.\u0026#xA;2. warn-only policy_mode masks the failure: the worker keeps polling and looks alive (loop.idle every 50s) but never claims anything. Operator has no signal beyond tailing the agent-loop log.\u0026#xA;3. The \u0026#39;suggested_action\u0026#39; text (\u0026#39;check the readiness route or harness configuration and retry\u0026#39;) is not actionable for the operator — the actual fault is in DDx\u0026#39;s own decoder, not in the route or harness config.\u0026#xA;4. Same-fingerprint repeat: 100% of attempts produce the same error code; the worker should escalate to FAIL after N consecutive identical warn-only fingerprints instead of looping silently.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;A. Decoder tolerance: accept verdict as bool, string, or both; coerce to a canonical representation. Add a regression test against a payload with verdict=true/false and verdict=\u0026#34;ready\u0026#34;/\u0026#34;not_ready\u0026#34;.\u0026#xA;B. Producer-side schema lock: pin the readiness_checks JSON schema in a shared place that both producer and consumer reference; CI gate that fails on drift.\u0026#xA;C. Same-fingerprint escalation: when the pre_claim_intake produces the same warn fingerprint on N (default 5) consecutive attempts across distinct bead_ids, escalate to operator-attention with the fingerprint and a single example payload. Do not keep silently looping.\u0026#xA;D. policy_mode=\u0026#39;warn-only\u0026#39; must not mask a 100% failure rate. Add a per-fingerprint counter and a guard.\u0026#xA;E. ddx work --watch should emit a top-level operator-visible message (stderr or status command) when its claim success rate over a rolling window falls below a threshold (e.g., 0% over 10 attempts) — silent idle on a full queue is a stuck state masquerading as healthy.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;CROSS-REF\u0026#xA;Adjacent bugs filed in this session: ddx-57c40485 (index.lock held minutes); ddx-8f2e0ebf (worker wedges on route resolution). All three share a theme: silent failures inside the worker that look healthy from the outside. The user is currently unable to make progress on the AR-2026-05-17 follow-up beads because of this.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. pre_claim_intake decoder accepts readiness_checks.verdict as JSON bool, JSON string, or absent; coerces to a documented canonical form. Unit test covers all three. Verified by a focused decoder test in the pre-claim intake package.\u0026#xA;2. CI schema gate: the readiness_checks JSON schema is defined in a shared place; producer and consumer both consume it; CI fails on schema drift.\u0026#xA;3. Same-fingerprint escalation: after N (default 5) consecutive warn outcomes with the same fingerprint, the worker emits an operator-attention event and stops looping silently. Tested by injecting a faulty readiness payload and asserting the escalation.\u0026#xA;4. Operator-visible signal: ddx work --watch surfaces (via stderr or \u0026#39;ddx bead status\u0026#39; or a new \u0026#39;ddx work status\u0026#39; subcommand) a warning when claim success rate over a configurable rolling window (default 10 attempts) drops below a configurable threshold.\u0026#xA;5. Documentation: ddx README names the pre-claim intake contract, the failure-class mapping (warn vs operator-attention vs hard error), and how operators should diagnose silent-idle.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003cnotes\u003e\ndecomposed into ddx-606fe854 (decoder verdict bool/string/absent), ddx-d67f124e (consecutive-fingerprint escalation), ddx-977e1a7f (claim-success-rate signal), ddx-c5d485c9 (CI schema gate), ddx-757a3344 (docs)\n    \u003c/notes\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003earea:execute-bead, area:pre-claim, area:workers, kind:bug, kind:reliability, observability, priority:reliability, severity:high, ac-quality:needs-refinement\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata base-rev=\"6b187d627ee6835c8a0757c0b463f5931eebb653\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260527T092129-ee89e738\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cnote\u003eNo governing references were pre-resolved. The bead description above is the primary contract. If it names files, specs, or prior beads, read them first. Ground decisions in repository state; do not guess.\u003c/note\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","GIT_CONFIG_GLOBAL":"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-f9ddaa68-20260527T092129-ee89e738/.ddx/executions/20260527T092129-ee89e738/embedded/git-global.cfg","GIT_CONFIG_SYSTEM":"/dev/null","PATH":"/Users/erik/Projects/.ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-f9ddaa68-20260527T092129-ee89e738/.ddx/executions/20260527T092129-ee89e738/embedded/git-bin:/usr/local/cuda/bin:/home/erik/.jbang/bin:/home/erik/.opencode/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/installs/bun/1.3.11/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/installs/node/22.21.1/bin:/Users/erik/.antigravity/antigravity/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/shims:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/home/erik/.local/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/git-subrepo/lib:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/Applications/SnowSQL.app/Contents/MacOS:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/Users/erik/.antigravity/antigravity/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/erik/.local/share/mise/shims:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/home/erik/.local/bin:/home/erik/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/git-subrepo/lib:/home/erik/.local/share/coursier/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/git-fuzzy/bin:/home/erik/go/bin:/home/erik/.dotfiles/scripts:/home/erik/.local/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/Applications/SnowSQL.app/Contents/MacOS:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin:/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/sbin:/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin:/usr/games:/usr/local/games:/snap/bin:/Users/erik/Library/Application Support/JetBrains/Toolbox/scripts:/Users/erik/Library/Application Support/Coursier/bin:/home/erik/.lmstudio/bin:/home/erik/.cache/lm-studio/bin:/home/erik/.local/bin:/Users/erik/.cache/lm-studio/bin:/Users/erik/Library/Application Support/JetBrains/Toolbox/scripts:/Users/erik/Library/Application Support/Coursier/bin:/home/erik/.lmstudio/bin:/home/erik/.cache/lm-studio/bin:/home/erik/.local/bin:/Users/erik/.cache/lm-studio/bin:/home/erik/.cargo/bin:/usr/local/cuda/bin:/home/erik/.jbang/bin:/home/erik/.opencode/bin:/Users/erik/.lmstudio/bin:/Users/erik/.lmstudio/bin:/home/erik/.claude/plugins/cache/claude-plugins-official/rust-analyzer-lsp/1.0.0/bin:/home/erik/.claude/plugins/cache/claude-plugins-official/frontend-design/unknown/bin","attempt_id":"20260527T092129-ee89e738","base_rev":"6b187d627ee6835c8a0757c0b463f5931eebb653","bead_id":"ddx-f9ddaa68","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260527T092129-ee89e738","correlation_id":"ddx-f9ddaa68:20260527T092129-ee89e738","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260527T092129-ee89e738/prompt.md","prompt_sha":"c39a18a78c19c0255012371c0fdf95da0967c32f715df2542cea497ea2afde6d","role":"implementer"